
To update this fork to the latest from the main GRDB project:

Information sources:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7244321/how-do-i-update-a-github-forked-repository
https://docs.github.com/en/free-pro-team@latest/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/syncing-a-fork
https://medium.com/@sahoosunilkumar/how-to-update-a-fork-in-git-95a7daadc14e

Go to the console prompt in the root of the project

git fetch upstream
git checkout master
git merge upstream/master
git push

Depending on how the GRDB-Fork project is used (and if versioning is required) you will have to apply a NEW tag to the master branch and push it so that SPM can see the merged changes elsewhere.


